In a small skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add 1/4 cup walnuts and brown sugar; stir until sugar is melted. Add bananas; cook and fold gently 1 to 2 minutes or until bananas are coated. Stir in orange juice. Cook an additional minute or until liquid is thick and syrupy. Remove from heat. Set aside 4 banana slices for garnish. Chop granola Spoon bananas, granola, and yogurt, alternating layers, into 4 parfait glasses to serve sundae style. Garnish each serving with 1 teaspoon walnuts, 2 teaspoons chopped granola and 1 banana slice. Serve at once.